com.cubeia.firebase.server.lobby.systemstate
Interface StateLobbyMBean

public interface StateLobbyMBean

This MBean is attached to the lobby in a Firebase system. It contains method for changing the broadcast period of the lobby.

Author:
Larsan

Method Detail

dumpSubscriptionInfoToLog

void dumpSubscriptionInfoToLog()
This method prints information of the lobby subscription to the server log. This subscription contains paths and object information. Use with care as this method is fairly resource demanding.

printSubscriptionInfo

String printSubscriptionInfo()
This method returns information of the lobby subscription. This subscription contains paths and object information. Use with care as this method is fairly resource demanding.

                            int area,

This method returns the number of subscriptions for a particular path.

getBroadcastPeriod

long getBroadcastPeriod()
This method return the broadcast period in milliseconds. The broadcast period is the interval in which Firebase sends lobby information to the clients.

Returns:
The broadcast period in milliseconds

setBroadcastPeriod

void setBroadcastPeriod(long millis)
This method changes the broadcast period, the interval between lobby broadcasts.

Parameters:
millis - The interval in milliseconds

getTableUpdatesPerSecond

int getTableUpdatesPerSecond()
This method returns the approximate number of change that have been recorded for tables in the lobby per second.

Returns:
The number of table changes per second

pause

void pause()
This method temporarily halts the broadcast of lobby changes to all clients. In effect the lobby will stop updating for all connected clients.

unpause

void unpause()
If the lobby is paused, this method un-pauses it.

isPaused

boolean isPaused()
Checks if the lobby is paused or not.

Returns:
True if the lobby is paused, false if not
